-===Carpathian Ruthenia===
+===Carpathian Ruthenia (Red bear)===
 {{main|Coat of arms of Carpathian Ruthenia}}

 The coat of arms was created after the end of the [[First World War]], when Carpathian Ruthenia (then called Subcarpathian Rus') was transferred from [[Kingdom of Hungary (1920–46)|Hungary]] to the newly created state of [[Czechoslovakia]]. It was designed in 1920 by [[Czechs|Czech]] historian {{ill|Gustav Friedrich|WD=Q12018531}}. The [[Rusyns|Ruthenians]] had been promised autonomy within the new country, and therefore a coat of arms was created for their land.{{citation needed|date=June 2014}}

